1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,717
For many Deaf and hard-of-hearing people, a

2
00:00:02,717 --> 00:00:05,435
simple phone-only task can become a barrier.

3
00:00:05,435 --> 00:00:08,540
Call Assist makes the conversation readable and controllable.

4
00:00:08,540 --> 00:00:11,487
It is a supervised, text-first calling copilot.

5
00:00:11,487 --> 00:00:14,433
The user sets the destination, goal, facts

6
00:00:14,433 --> 00:00:17,380
that may be shared, and hard boundaries.

7
00:00:17,380 --> 00:00:22,010
The assistant handles the conversation, but the user keeps final control.

8
00:00:22,010 --> 00:00:25,512
Here, Maya wants to reserve a quiet library room.

9
00:00:25,512 --> 00:00:29,015
She approves only the minimum facts the assistant needs

10
00:00:29,015 --> 00:00:32,128
and forbids fees, payments, or new personal details.

11
00:00:32,128 --> 00:00:35,630
She confirms that this is a user-initiated, low-risk call.

12
00:00:35,630 --> 00:00:40,803
For reliable public judging, this site deliberately simulates the GPT-5.6 planning

13
00:00:40,803 --> 00:00:45,505
stages and uses the same structured contract without external credentials.

14
00:00:45,505 --> 00:00:50,208
In configured mode, the OpenAI Responses API uses GPT-5.6 Sol

15
00:00:50,208 --> 00:00:54,910
to turn approved facts and boundaries into a reviewable plan.

16
00:00:54,910 --> 00:00:56,698
Nothing happens before review.

17
00:00:56,698 --> 00:00:59,828
Maya can check the objective, conversation path,

18
00:00:59,828 --> 00:01:02,511
success criteria, and every approval gate.

19
00:01:02,511 --> 00:01:07,429
The opening identifies Call Assist as an AI accessibility assistant and

20
00:01:07,429 --> 00:01:11,900
asks affirmative consent before live transcription and temporary text review.

21
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:15,326
What you are about to see is a judge-safe simulation;

22
00:01:15,326 --> 00:01:17,725
it does not place a phone call.

23
00:01:17,725 --> 00:01:20,809
The Twilio and OpenAI Realtime path is implemented and

24
00:01:20,809 --> 00:01:23,550
has been tested with a consented, allowlisted destination.

25
00:01:23,550 --> 00:01:27,175
Rather than pressure the person answering with a checklist, Call

26
00:01:27,175 --> 00:01:30,800
Assist explains that it is helping someone use live captions,

27
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,425
asks one warm consent question, and then uses the plan

28
00:01:34,425 --> 00:01:38,050
to make reasonable low-risk choices while keeping the exchange natural.

29
00:01:38,050 --> 00:01:41,824
Maya can pause without speaking, type what Call Assist should

30
00:01:41,824 --> 00:01:45,220
say, correct a detail, resume, or end the call.

31
00:01:45,220 --> 00:01:48,994
Large two-speaker captions clearly separate the business from the assistant,

32
00:01:48,994 --> 00:01:52,390
so she can follow the conversation at a glance.

33
00:01:52,390 --> 00:01:56,305
When the library offers the room, Call Assist stops.

34
00:01:56,305 --> 00:01:58,915
Nothing is committed until Maya chooses.

35
00:01:58,915 --> 00:02:04,135
Payments, emergencies, marketing, and high-stakes medical or financial calls are blocked entirely;

36
00:02:04,135 --> 00:02:07,180
this first release stays deliberately low risk.

37
00:02:07,180 --> 00:02:11,033
After the call, Maya gets confirmed details, the reference

38
00:02:11,033 --> 00:02:14,886
number, next actions, and the full conversation for review.

39
00:02:14,886 --> 00:02:17,882
In configured mode, GPT-5.6 structures this outcome.

40
00:02:17,882 --> 00:02:19,595
No audio is recorded;

41
00:02:19,595 --> 00:02:22,591
the text remains only in this browser

42
00:02:22,591 --> 00:02:25,160
tab and can be cleared explicitly.

43
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:30,440
Codex helped me implement and test the accessible React interface,

44
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:35,192
safety guardrails, GPT-5.6 integration, and the Twilio-to-OpenAI Realtime bridge.

45
00:02:35,192 --> 00:02:38,360
Call Assist makes phone calls readable.
